edu.ucla.sspace.graph.isomorphism

Class TypedVF2IsomorphismTester

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ucla.sspace.graph.isomorphism.AbstractIsomorphismTester
      • edu.ucla.sspace.graph.isomorphism.TypedVF2IsomorphismTester
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IsomorphismTester

    public class TypedVF2IsomorphismTester
extends AbstractIsomorphismTester
    An extension of the VF2 algorithm for detecting isomorphic graphs that tests for edge type equivalance. The VF2 algorithm may be found in:
    • Luigi P. Cordella, Pasquale Foggia, Carlo Sansone, and Mario Vento. A (Sub)Graph Isomorphism Algorithm for Matching Large Graphs. IEEE Transactions on Pattern Analysis and Machine Intelligence, 26:10. 2004. Available here
    This class checks for both structural and edge type equivalence between two graphs. If the graphs are not instances of Multigraph or have a single edge type, this class is equivalent in functionality to the original VF2 algorithm.

    This implementation is an adaptation of the VFLib implementation.

    This class is thread-safe.

    Author:
    David Jurgens
